In Pain Square~
The scortched earth here seems to eminate a deep red glow.  The air is cold
and cutting against your exposed flesh.  The wall of the building to the 
north is cold and black.  It seems to be cut from a single block of pitch
black stone.  Every inch of its surface is covered with deeply carved runes
of power.  One symbol stands out in grey among the intricate web of 
power runes.  It is repeated more times than you care to count.  It looks
vaguely like an eight laid on its side.  It is the symbol for infinity.
The carving is not only on the wall but seems to spill off onto the ground
at its base.  The grooves and swirles continue for a number of feet away
from the structure itself.  A small trickle of water can be seen gathering
in some of the deeper runes carved into the ground.  The water is blood red
and seems to contain flecks of gold or silver, which, you cannot tell.
There is no plantlife at all here.  The only signs of life are the structures
that must have been built by the greatest artisans to ever walk these realms.
The water is now slowly overfilling the deep grooves cut in the ground and
is beginning to ooze toward your feet.  It smells of urine and rust and does
not seep into the ground but skates on the surface as if afraid to touch it.
To the north, set into the black wall, is a huge Iron gate.  The bars to
each side are set into the charred stone.  Nothing but forboding darkness
can be seen through the bars.
~
